cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with depth estimation from monocular endoscopy data using convolutional neural networks.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as endoscopy is a common tool in robotic surgery and the proposed method could be useful in improving the accuracy of robotic surgery.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach for training the neural network.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with developing an AI-based method for dense depth estimation.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with processing and analyzing endoscopic videos.
